        <page n="01" image="va.au.ss.1869.12.28.01" exists="no">
            <div type="a">
                <column>02</column>
                <head>The Stay Law Again</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <transcript>
                    <p/>
                </transcript>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>General Canby issued an order extending the Stay Law until ten days after
                    publication of the approval by Congress of the Constitution ratified by the
                    voters of Virginia.</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>02</column>
                <head>Virginia Ain't in the Union Yet</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <transcript>
                    <p/>
                </transcript>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>The editor lamented that Congress still had not re-admitted Virginia to the
                    Union. "A few Virginians, and others from this Commonwealth, have been for days
                    licking the blacking from the boots of Butler and offering themselves as
                    spittoons for Radical expectoration without accomplishing any good for
                    themselves or the State."</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
            <pageNote/>
        </page>
